You can check the `result` in the callback to ensure that the request didn&#39;t fall back to HTTP/1.1 though:
```
result.getVersion().equals(2,0)
```
will get you the information.

Be aware, that this code above (and yours) will open a new HTTPContext for every `execute`. Therefore, no interleaving calls will be made within this TCP connection which is what HTTP/2.0 is all about.

You have to create a HTTPContext first and use this context in every call to `execute`.

